<div class="mx-auto text-justify lg:p-8">
  <h1
    class="mb-3 mt-8 font-header text-3xl font-bold md:text-5xl lg:mb-12"
    id="how_to_participate"
  >
    How to participate in the Review Club
  </h1>

  <p class="my-5 text-base md:text-base lg:text-2xl">
    <span class="font-bold text-orange"
      >Step 1: Stay Updated</span
    >
  </p>
  <ul
    class="ml-10 list-disc text-base md:text-base lg:text-2xl"
  >
    <li>
      Join our <a href="#" class="underline">Discord</a> and
      follow the Review Club channel for updates.
    </li>
    <li>
      The club meets every other Thursday at 8:00 PM IST in
      the Lounge voice channel on Discord.
    </li>
    <li>
      Follow our <a href="#" class="underline"
        >GitHub repository</a
      > for study materials and PR details.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <p class="my-5 text-base md:text-base lg:text-2xl">
    <span class="font-bold text-orange"
      >Step 2: Prepare for the discussion</span
    >
  </p>
  <ul
    class="ml-10 list-disc text-base md:text-base lg:text-2xl"
  >
    <li>
      Read the PR summary and discussion questions posted on


      <a href="#" class="underline">GitHub issues</a>.
    </li>
    <li>
      Review the code changes and prepare your thoughts.
    </li>
    <li>
      Ask questions in the Discord channel as you study.
      Questions are always welcome!
    </li>
  </ul>

  <p class="my-5 text-base md:text-base lg:text-2xl">
    A full list of prerequisites is available in the <a
      href="#"
      class="underline">GitHub README</a
    >, so make sure to check that out before your first
    session.
  </p>

  <p class="my-5 text-base md:text-base lg:text-2xl">
    <span class="font-bold text-orange"
      >Step 3: Join the Club Discussion</span
    >
  </p>
  <ul
    class="ml-10 list-disc text-base md:text-base lg:text-2xl"
  >
    <li>
      The club is discussion-driven, not a lecture. A host
      guides the session.
    </li>
    <li>
      You are expected to critically analyze the PR, ask
      questions, and provide feedback.
    </li>
    <li>
      Discussions are recorded and uploaded to YouTube for
      reference.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <p class="my-5 text-base md:text-base lg:text-2xl">
    <span class="font-bold text-orange"
      >Step 4: Submit Your Review</span
    >
  </p>
  <ul
    class="ml-10 list-disc text-base md:text-base lg:text-2xl"
  >
    <li>
      After the club session, submit your review on the
      Bitcoin Core PR thread.
    </li>
    <li>
      This helps you build your Proof of Work and develop as
      a Bitcoin Core contributor.
    </li>
  </ul>
</div>
